(The Director Who Disappeared, The Story of The Ninja Mission)

Swedish documentary on B-movie director Mats Helge Olsson.

My opinion on the docu: it's interesting with great interviews
and old footage. However it doesn't nearly cover his career and
all the movies he did. It's full of hyperbole (everything is the
greatest and most successful etc) and all the 80s pop music
is pretty weird. You also never get a real sense of when all
this was happening, the only date given is 1983 as the
shooting year of The Ninja Mission.
It's still absolutely worth a watch and then go grab some
of the mans films and have a good time.

Video: H264 1280x720 25fps
Audio: Swedish AAC 48000Hz stereo
Subtitles: English fansub by myself.
